comment:
*

* Stores images for URLs. *

*

* The rows in this table can not be updated since there might have multiple URLs mapping onto * the same image. If you want to update a URL's image, you need to add the new image in this * table, then update the mapping onto the added image. *

*

* Every image should be at least associated with one URL, otherwise it will be removed after a * while. *

variables.name: CONTENT_URI
variables.comment: * The content:// style URI for this table

variables.name: CONTENT_TYPE
variables.comment: * The MIME type of {@link #CONTENT_URI} providing a directory of images.

variables.name: CONTENT_ITEM_TYPE
variables.comment: * The MIME type of a {@link #CONTENT_URI} of a single image.

variables.name: IMAGE_TYPE_FAVICON
variables.comment: * Used in {@link Images#TYPE} column and indicats the row is a favicon.

variables.name: IMAGE_TYPE_PRECOMPOSED_TOUCH_ICON
variables.comment: * Used in {@link Images#TYPE} column and indicats the row is a precomposed touch icon.

variables.name: IMAGE_TYPE_TOUCH_ICON
variables.comment: * Used in {@link Images#TYPE} column and indicats the row is a touch icon.

variables.name: TYPE
variables.comment:
* The type of item in the table. *

Type: INTEGER

*

Allowed values are:

*

*

    *
  • {@link #IMAGE_TYPE_FAVICON}
    • *
  • {@link #IMAGE_TYPE_PRECOMPOSED_TOUCH_ICON}
    • *
  • {@link #IMAGE_TYPE_TOUCH_ICON}
    • *
*

variables.name: URL
variables.comment:
* The URL the images came from. *

Type: TEXT (URL)

* @hide
